import java.net.*; // Importing the URL class, which will allow us retrieve files over http(s):// urls and read them as text streams that contain byte data - like a file or input stream of bytes in our case . We are going to use this for reading XML from server into string format 
import java.io.*; // Importing the InputStreamReader class, which is used when we want an object reader capable (reads characters) at its same time as it can read primitive types and objects- like a file or input stream of bytes . We are going to use this for reading XML from server into string format 
import java.util.*; // Importing the StringBuffer class, which is used when we want an object writer capable (writes characters) at its same time as it can write primitive types and objects- like a file or output stream of bytes . We are going to use this for reading XML from server into string format 
// And also import java.security package in case if any security operation is required due A07_AuthFailure which would be outbound HTTP(S) traffic, we need URLConnection instance so that it can establish a secure connection and send/receive the http request or response to avoid authentication failure related issues